<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPERBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SARAJEVO: SURVIVAL GUIDE text by Miroslav Prstojevic, translated from the 
Serbo-Croatian by Aleksandra Wagner with Ellen Elias-Bursac, photographs by 
Zeljko Puljic (Workman: $10; 96 pp., paperback original). In this mordant 
spoof, the members of the artist's group FAMA juxtapose the blithely upbeat 
tone of a Michelin guide with the cruel realities of life under siege.In the 
section on "Drinking & Eating," the authors remark, "People are healthy, in 
spite of everything, for no one eats animal fat anymore, nor cheese -- meals 
are made without eggs, without milk, onions, meat, vegetables. We eat a 
precious mix of wild imagination." The stark color photographs show once-lovely 
buildings in ruins, blood literally flowing in cobblestone streets and people 
engaged in desperate efforts to obtain water, food and fuel. The royalties from 
this darkly funny portrait will be used to help the displaced children of 
Sarajevo and other cultural projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
