<P>
 THE FIFTIES: A Women's Oral History by Brett Harvey (HarperPerennial: $12; 228 
pp.) . Free-lance journalist Brett Harvey spoke to 92 women about work, sex, 
marriage, politics, education and motherhood. A surprising number of the women 
felt they drifted through the key decisions in their lives, rather than 
consciously made them: It was easier to do what was expected than to fight the 
system. Some of their memories seem so remote, it's difficult to believe only 
40 years have a elapsed. 
