</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ANOTHER TRIBUTE?: The latest tribute album in the works actually has a few 
surprises to offer. It's a collection of artists honoring the Carpenters, and 
the roster of acts signed up might not be what you'd expected.Committed to the 
project already are Sonic Youth, Redd Kross, American Music Club, the 
Cranberries, Bettie Serveert and Shonen Knife. 
</P>
<P>
 The album, the brainchild of rock journalist David Kojoyan and producer Matt 
Wallace, will be released later this year by A&M to mark the 25th anniversary 
of the Carpenters' signing with the company. An A&M spokeswoman insists that it 
is a loving tribute by rockers who truly like the brother-and-sister duo's 
music. Sonic Youth fans will recall the song "Tunic (Song for Karen)" from the 
band's album "Goo," in which Kim Gordon portrays the late Karen Carpenter, who 
died in 1983 after bouts with anorexia nervosa, reassuring her family that 
she's doing fine in the afterlife.  
</P>
<P>
 One thing remains to be decided: Which groups will get to sing the Carpenters' 
most-loved hits, "Close to You" and "Superstar"? Steve Hochman 
</P>
</TEXT>
