<P>
 * * * Various artists, "Above the Rim" soundtrack, Death Row/Interscope. 
2Pac's intense, touching "Pain" is one of the year's best rap songs, and his 
collaboration with Treach and Riddler on "Loyal to the Game" isn't far 
behind.Also exceptional: B Rezell's breezy commentary on pot-smoking, "Blowed 
Away." The only wretched track: Al B. Sure!'s "I'm Still in Love With You." 
Most of the 21 gangsta rap and racy, mid-tempo R&B tracks are above average. 
