<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' PICKS: 'HOMEWARD BOUND: THE INCREDIBLE JOURNEY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This 1993 Disney release is a fine family film, a vast improvement over the 
1963 version.This time, the tale of three pets who make their way through a 
forest wilderness provides voices for a wise and mature golden retriever, a 
frisky bulldog puppy and a fastidious Himalayan cat. And it involves the 
family, who left them behind temporarily with a friend. A skillful job all 
around, especially by director Duwayne Dunham and writers Caroline Thompson and 
Linda Woolverton. Robert Hays and Kim Greist star (Disney Channel Monday at 
1:05 a.m.). Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</TEXT>
