<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AND ONE MORE THING: "Rock Talk," a new book collecting amusing quotes by and 
about rockers, includes, among other things, a whole short chapter on "Guitar 
Smashing 101." Quoted, naturally, on the subject of instrument destroying are 
the likes of Pete Townshend and Kurt Cobain. But also represented is Les Paul, 
the inventor of the electric guitar, who says of the smashing: "I encourage 
them because they have to go out and buy more guitars." 
</P>
</TEXT>
