<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' PICKS: 'THE FEAR INSIDE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Ray Loynd 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two psycho lovers, Dylan McDermott and Jennifer Rubin, terrorize a woman, 
Christine Lahti (left, with Rubin) who suffers from agoraphobia in this 1992 
cable production.A cut or two above most suspense stories because of the 
gripping performances under Leon Ichaso's direction and a script (by David 
Birke) that puts a twist on the old premise of a victim trapped in her house. 
Posing as brother and sister, McDermott and Rubin ingratiate themselves into 
Lahti's life and her spacious, isolated home. Recently separated, she is 
seeking companionship to alleviate her irrational fear of the outdoors (USA 
Thursday at 9 p.m.). Ray Loynd 
</P>
</TEXT>
