<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO REWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ted Bessell plays Mary's new, affectionate boyfriend on The Mary Tyler Moore 
Show (Sunday at 10 p.m. on Nickelodeon). He also appears on Tuesday's episode 
at 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Suzanne Pleshette guest stars on Columbo (Monday at 12:30 p.m. on A&E) in an 
episode in which an unstable murder witness complicates his case against 
America's leading war hero. 
</P>
<P>
 Biography (Tuesday at 5 and 9 p.m. on A&E) looks at the legendary Sid Caesar. 
Included are clips from his 1950s series "Your Show of Shows" and interviews 
with Carl Reiner and Mel Brooks. 
</P>
<P>
 Before the force was with him, "Star Wars's" Mark Hamill appeared on The 
Partridge Family (Tuesday at 8 p.m. on Nickelodeon) in an episode in which 
Laurie gets braces. 
</P>
<P>
 Set your VCR's for the classic "Job Switching" episode of I Love Lucy (Tuesday 
at 9 p.m. on Nickelodeon). Lucy and Ethel get jobs at a candy factory and are 
forced to work the conveyor belt. 
</P>
<P>
 Pat O'Brien, Walter Brennan and Edgar Buchanan star in the charming The 
Over-the-Hill-Gang (Tuesday at 10:35 p.m. on TBS), 1969 TV movie about a group 
of retired Texas Rangers who attempt to bring law and order to a Western town 
run by a corrupt mayor. 
</P>
<P>
 David Janssen plays a veteran cop who becomes too emotionally involved in his 
job on a two-part Police Story (Thursday and Friday at 2 p.m. on A&E). 
</P>
<P>
 Howard Hesseman appears on two episodes of The Bob Newhart Show (Thursday and 
Friday at 9:30 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Mary's arrogant Aunt Flo (Eileen Heckhart) returns on The Mary Tyler Moore 
Show (Friday at 10:30 p.m. on Nickelodeon). Heckhart currently makes guest 
appearances on "Love & War" as Jake Stein's (Jay Thomas) mother. 
</P>
<P>
 Very Very Nick at Nite (Saturday at 10 p.m. on Nickelodeon) presents "Very 
Very Get Rich Quick," which features Nick at Nite characters scheming to get 
money in a big hurry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
