<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; CALIFORNIA CORNER; FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 OJAI -- Art meets horticulture at the Ojai Valley Garden Club's Flower Show 
and Sale, next Saturday and Sunday at the Ojai Valley Women's Club, 441 E. Ojai 
Ave. Noon-5 p.m. Saturday; 11 a.m.-5 p.m. next Sunday. (805) 640-8171. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN FRANCISCO -- The Cherry Blossom Festival is next Saturday and Sunday and 
April 23-24 at the Japan Center (Post and Buchanan streets) and the neighboring 
blocks of Japantown. The festival starts at 11 a.m. daily; most events are 
free. A parade is at 1 p.m. April 24. (415) 563-2313. 
</P>
<P>
 COSTA MESA -- Inclined toward the equine? A Miniature Horse Show is 8 a.m.-5 
p.m. Saturday and Sunday in the Equestrian Center at the Orange County Fair and 
Exposition Center, 88 Fair Drive. A Spring Hunter/Jumper Horse Show is 8 a.m.-5 
p.m. April 22-24, also in the Equestrian Center. Both shows are free. (714) 
708-1652. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN LUIS OBISPO -- Celebrate spring's bounty at the third annual Garden 
Festival, 10 a.m.-4 p.m. next Sunday at El Chorro Regional Park. Featured: 
Walks, gardening demonstrations and children's crafts. $1; free for kids under 
12. On California 1 across from Cuesta College. (805) 546-3501. 
</P>
<P>
 STOCKTON -- Delicious activities await at the Stockton Asparagus Festival IX, 
1:30-7 p.m. April 22; 10 a.m.-7 p.m. April 23-24 at Oak Grove Regional Park, 
Eight Mile Road and I-5. A Fun Run is at 8:30 a.m. Sunday. $6, general; $3, 
kids 6-12 and seniors 60 and over. (209) 466-6674. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
