<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPTIONS IN IDYLLWILD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The letter writer who was dismayed about the Idyllwild Gastronome's "locals 
only" attitude was right on target (Letters, March 20.)My family has been 
visiting Idyllwild since 1957. It is home to many retired people on fixed 
incomes, and if the Gastronome had to rely on their minuscule pensions, it 
would close in about a week. This little cafe really takes itself seriously, 
but it is a relative upstart compared to other local eateries. For friendly 
service and great food, visitors should join the locals at the Bread Basket. 
</P>
<P>
 LEONORA HOLDER 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
