<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SCATTERED SHOWERS LEAD TO HANDFUL OF ACCIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scattered showers across Ventura County early Saturday morning caught 
motorists by surprise, but the rain gave way to sunshine and gusty winds.  
</P>
<P>
 Clear skies are expected today, with temperatures in the upper 60s along the 
coast and lower 70s inland, forecasters said. 
</P>
<P>
 A small-craft warning for winds of 15 to 25 m.p.h. could continue today, Coast 
Guard officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The storm deposited 1/10 to a quarter inch of rain from Santa Barbara to 
Orange counties. 
</P>
<P>
 The wet roads caused a handful of traffic accidents early Saturday morning, 
police officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura Police Department reported three non-injury accidents between 9 
and 10 a.m., and the Simi Valley Police Department reported two accidents about 
the same time.  
</P>
<P>
 "It's kind of unusual for a Saturday morning to have that many," Ventura 
Police Officer Kelly Dean said. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
