<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE VOLLEYBALL; UCLA REBOUNDS TO DOWN USC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UCLA started slowly but gained momentum in a 12-15, 15-11, 15-8, 15-8 victory 
over USC in the final of the UCLA volleyball tournament Saturday at Pauley 
Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Nygaard had 27 kills and nine blocks and Tim Kelly added 10 blocks to 
lead the top-ranked Bruins (22-1) before a crowd of 1,061. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Underwood and Jason Mulholland had 33 kills each in a losing effort for 
fourth-ranked USC (15-5). 
</P>
<P>
 USC gained a 5-0 lead in the first game before the Bruins came back to tie it 
twice before finally losing the game. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third place game, fifth-ranked Cal State Northridge (15-9) defeated No. 
14 Loyola Marymount (6-19), 15-3, 15-13, 15-11. WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
