<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CARLSON LEADS OCC WOMEN TO DIVING TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Heidi Carlson placed first in the three-meter diving and second in the 
one-meter competition to lead the Orange Coast women's diving team to the 
championship of the Saddleback Diving Pentathlon Saturday at Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlson finished with an overall score of 391.00, well ahead of second-place 
Windy Kraynik of San Diego Mesa, who finished with 371.70.OCC's Tina Edwards 
was third at 370.90. The Pirates finished with 761.90 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Mesa won the men's title with 618.70 points and was led by Troy Velasco, the 
overall champion. Bill Tovar of OCC was fourth in the three-meter competition, 
with a score of 146.45. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's track and field: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 73, Golden West 56, San Diego Mesa 29 -- Francisco Vasquez won 
the 1,500 (4:11.7) and 5,000 (15:48.6), Ernie Wilson won the 100 (11.2) and 200 
(21.9) and Ty Wynn won the javelin (164-10) to help lead Rancho Santiago (7-1). 
Golden West is 4-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
