<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL ROUNDUP; HOT RIO MESA ROMPS TWICE PAST BELL-JEFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rio Mesa feasted off Bell-Jeff pitching Saturday, scoring 41 runs in a 
nonleague doubleheader at Rio Mesa. The Spartans won the first game, 11-4, 
behind Steve Arneson, who had three hits and four runs batted in, and Donald 
DiDomizio, who added four RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Rio Mesa pounded out 25 hits in the second game, a 30-3 romp. Marcus Yasutake 
had three hits including a home run and five RBIs. Vince Roman also had five 
RBIs for the Spartans (11-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura 1, Lompoc 0 -- Craig Gladstone (1-1) scattered seven hits over seven 
innings, striking out four, and Kevin Sass singled home Chris Cicuto with the 
nonleague game's only run in the third inning at Agoura. Sass, Cicuto and Matt 
Gershon each had two hits for Agoura (3-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Hueneme 5, St. Ignatius 4 -- Josh Towers' two-out triple drove in Manuel 
Aranda from first base with two out in the top of the seventh in the 
third-place game of the San Luis Obispo tournament as the Vikings improved to 
8-8. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany 2, Bloomington 1 -- Rex Supa slugged a solo home run in the sixth 
inning to break a 1-1 tie as Alemany (11-6) gained fifth place at the San Luis 
Obispo tournament. Jerry Najar (1-0) got the victory with two innings of 
one-hit relief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
