<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; LA QUINTA TIPS ARROYO GRANDE TO WIN TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Linda Rodriguez drove in Jaclyn Fredrickson with a one-out single in the 
fourth inning as La Quinta beat Arroyo Grande, 1-0, Saturday, winning the 
championship of the San Luis Obispo Tiger softball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelly McLaughlin (6-2) pitched a two-hitter, striking out four. 
</P>
<P>
 In the semifinals, La Quinta (10-4) beat Morro Bay, 8-1, as Jennifer Hollinger 
struck out nine. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Rosary 4-4, Buena Park 3-2 -- Nicola Walsh (5-0) won both games for visiting 
Rosary, striking out 12. She also had two triples in the first game, and had 
four hits and three runs scored in the doubleheader. 
</P>
<P>
 Shannon Sportsman also had four hits, with a double and a home run, and Regina 
Martin had a double, a triple, two singles, and the game-winning RBI in the 
first game for Rosary (8-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 20-7, Artesia 2-0 (first game 5, mercy) -- Geoff Wilson and 
Deric Yanigisawa hit grand slams to key a 16-run second inning in the first 
game for host Fountain Valley. Dan Hoppie hit another grand slam in the fourth 
inning, as the Barons had 14 hits. 
</P>
<P>
 In the second game, Chris Ponchak hit a homer and three pitchers combined on a 
two-hitter. Artesia had four hits in the two games. 
</P>
<P>
 Yanigisawa had four hits and six RBIs in the two games. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 100, San Diego University High 70 -- Mike Ciecek won the 500 
freestyle in 5:30.28 and the 100 breaststroke in 1:08.96 for Mater Dei (3-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 93, San Diego University High 77 -- Kim Wilson swam a personal best 
2:12.15 in the 200 freestyle for Mater Dei (2-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 3, Ocean View 2 -- Justin DeBlasio had 12 kills as visiting 
Santa Margarita rallied from a two-game deficit to win its first match of the 
year, 3-15, 12-15, 15-9, 15-13, 15-10. 
</P>
