<P>
PENDLETON TO HOLD SHELLING EXERCISES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 People living within 50 miles of Camp Pendleton should expect to hear sporadic 
explosions throughout the day on Monday because of shelling exercises at the 
base. 
</P>
<P>
 The explosions will be the result of 95-pound projectiles fired from 155mm 
howitzers in the middle of the base. Five surrounding communities -- San 
Clemente, Temecula, Fallbrook, Vista and Oceanside -- will probably feel 
rumblings in addition to hearing the explosions, which will last until 
midnight. 
</P>
<P>
 The shelling is part of monthly training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
