<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE WOUND DRIVER AFTER BRIEF CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A police officer shot and wounded a 25-year-old man who had tried to run over 
the officer and a partner with a car early Saturday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dinh The Nguyen, of Garden Grove, was arrested on suspicion of assault with a 
deadly weapon on a peace officer, evading a peace officer and driving under the 
influence of alcohol or drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Nguyen had been driving a car erratically with the headlights off 
about 2 a.m. That attracted the attention of Sgt. Scott Watson, who was 
patrolling a residential area near Lampson Avenue and 9th Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Watson tried to pull Nguyen's auto over but the driver fled in his car, Sgt. 
Joe Johnson said. A second officer in a patrol car joined the pursuit, and 
Nguyen led both into a cul-de-sac, he said. Police gave the following account: 
</P>
<P>
 When Nguyen pulled into the driveway of a home in the 11500 block of Dorada 
Avenue, officers blocked the exit with their patrol cars and got out to 
approach him. Nguyen then tried to escape, driving over a lawn between two 
trees and attempting to ram the officers. 
</P>
<P>
 The second officer -- whose name was not released -- fired one shot at Nguyen, 
grazing him in the lower arm. 
</P>
<P>
 Nguyen was treated and released from Garden Grove Hospital and Medical Center, 
Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
 A car, when used in such a way, may be considered a weapon, Johnson said, and 
department policy allows police officers to fire at a suspect if lives are at 
risk. 
</P>
<P>
 Nguyen was being held Saturday at Orange County Jail in lieu of $50,000 bail. 
He is scheduled to be arraigned Tuesday at West Orange County Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators from the district attorney's office are looking into the 
shooting, which is routine in officer-involved shootings in the county. 
</P>
</TEXT>
