<P>
HONORS FOR 'UNSUNG HEROES' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Japanese American Historical Society of Southern California is accepting 
nominations for its fourth annual community service and achievement awards, 
which recognize the "unsung heroes" in the community. 
</P>
<P>
 Nominees should be organizations or individuals who have served the Japanese 
American community or promoted the Japanese American heritage through cultural 
and artistic achievements.  
</P>
<P>
 Nominees can be from anywhere in Southern California and are not limited to 
Japanese Americans. The entry deadline is May 27. 
</P>
<P>
 Five winners will receive $500 each at an awards dinner in September.  
</P>
<P>
 Nomination forms: Iku Kiriyama at (310) 326-0608. 
