<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: SOUTH; TRAINING OFFERED TO ENTREPRENEURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Dunbar Economic Development Corp. is co-sponsoring a free six-month 
training course for entrepreneurs who live within the city's enterprise zones. 
</P>
<P>
 The weekly classes teach low- to moderate-income men and women learn to expand 
their businesses.Professionals volunteer their expertise in areas such as 
sales, taxes and advertising. 
</P>
<P>
 Classes begin May 14 at Dunbar, 4225 S. Central Ave., and are limited to 30 
people. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, co-sponsored by the California American Woman's Entrepreneurial 
Development Corp. and the city, is funded through private and public grants. 
</P>
<P>
 "This program is different because we're going right into the community, and 
we are working with Dunbar to help rebuild that area of the city," said Patti 
Koltnow, a spokeswoman for the state women's group. 
</P>
<P>
 "We will hope to not only bring in training, but for those who complete the 
program successfully, we hope to set up some type of access to capital through 
Dunbar and the Community Financial Resource Center."  
</P>
<P>
 Applicants must live within the city, have operated their business for at 
least one year, and be grossing at least $35,000 a year. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: Patti Koltnow at (310) 983-3747. 
</P>
