<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: SOUTH-CENTRAL; WEINGART Y HOLDS FREE HEALTH COURSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SANDRA HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Weingart Urban Center YMCA is sponsoring free health education courses as 
part of its monthlong 10th anniversary celebration this month. 
</P>
<P>
 The courses -- on weight loss, blood pressure control and diabetes -- will 
start Monday in the newly renovated health and fitness center. 
</P>
<P>
 The Weingart YMCA will sponsor an April 16 music festival featuring local 
youth choirs at USC's Annenberg School of Communication. Also scheduled is a 
free April 23 health clinic, which will include immunizations, dental 
check-ups, and eye and health exams. 
</P>
<P>
 The center, at 9900 S. Vermont Ave., renovated its fitness center after 
raising more than $100,000 during a three-month fund drive. "This community has 
a higher need than most others for fitness, (which) most people think is a 
recreational thing. But people have a far greater need to be involved in 
preventive medicine," said Robert Wilkins, executive director of the Weingart 
YMCA. "People think poor folk have a greater agenda. They think, 'You need to 
learn to read before you get around to lifting weights or running around a 
track.' 
</P>
<P>
 "We are doing this to mark our agenda for the next 10 years as we become more 
proactive as a health care provider in terms of fitness," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 754-3191. SANDRA HERNANDEZ 
</P>
