<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: LINCOLN HEIGHTS; CONCERT TO HELP PAY BILLS FOR ILL BOY, 
13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY ANNE PEREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An eclectic group of performers and musicians will gather Friday at Plaza de 
la Raza to raise money for a 13-year-old poet with Epstein-Barr syndrome. 
</P>
<P>
 Ehecatl Chumacero of Pasadena received the diagnosis one month ago and has 
missed two months of school, said his mother, Olivia Chumacero.Ehecatl, who 
attended Washington Middle School, has undergone physical therapy and requires 
more medical attention. His medical bills have already reached $4,000 and will 
continue to rise, his mother said. 
</P>
<P>
 Chumacero, the mother of two, has no insurance. 
</P>
<P>
 "The doctor told us they don't have any Western cure for this, and they tell 
him to rest and eat well," said Chumacero, a writer and teacher of film and 
theater at Mujeres y Hombres Nobles, an alternative school in East Los Angeles. 
"I've met other people who have dealt with this and I'm trying to find out 
what's best for him." 
</P>
<P>
 The performers, including Luis Alfaro, host Diane Rodriguez and members of 
Latins Anonymous and Culture Clash, are friends of Chumacero's and have agreed 
to help. Other performers include Evelina Fernandez, Maria Elena Gaitan and the 
singing group Los Jalapenos. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $15 for the show, which begins at 8 p.m. Plaza de la Raza is at 
3540 Mission Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations: (818) 564-1546. MARY ANNE PEREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
