</P>
<P>
 Despite the problems they face, community members remain optimistic: 
</P>
<P>
 "It's like everybody comes here expecting to see dirty streets and gang-this 
and gang-that, but we don't want to live like that. We're human too." 
</P>
<P>
 - Floyd Frazer, 51, a 17-year resident 
